                                <div class="text-para">
                                    <p class="right-pera">Puppy biting, and mouthing is possibly one of the most
                                        challenging behaviours you’ll encounter and it lasts until they are around 6
                                        months old.</p>
                                    <p>Trying to prevent this behaviour is pointless. Puppies literally discover the
                                        world with their mouths. Biting and mouthing is their way of experiencing new
                                        things—and everything is new to a puppy! Rather than stamping the behaviour out,
                                        find ways to redirect it to more desirable targets, like toys, teething rings
                                        and treats. Giving them little meaty bones will strengthen their jaws and, while
                                        this may seem counterintuitive when you’re being bitten day and night, it will
                                        also mentally stimulate them, making for calm and content puppies.</p>
